1. Every function and variable in Java is contained in some class.

2. All classes, in turn, belong to some package. The Hello class belongs to the anonymous package.

3. Static methods and variables are “one-of” things.

4. Check if it is Prime: 

   private static boolean isDivisible(int x, int k) {  
        if (k >= x) // a "guard"
                      return false;
        else if (x % k == 0) // "%" means "remainder"
                      return true;
        else // if (k < x && x % k != 0)
                      return isDivisible(x, k+1);
    }
    
5. From Recursive to Iteration 
   
   /* Recursive */
   if ( k >= x )
          return false;
   else if (x % k == 0)
          return true;
   else
          return isDivisible(x, k+1 );
          
   /* Iteration - 1 */
   while ( k < x ) {  
      if (x % k == 0)
          return true;
      k = k+1 ;
   }
   return false;
          
   /* Iteration - 2 */       
   for ( int k1 = k ; k1 < x ; k1 += 1 ) {
      if (x % k1 == 0)
      return true;
   }
   return false;
          
          
          
          
